{ This position is from the game below: Yiping Lou vs Jun Xu. I mark this as an important theme in the Accelerated Dragon because of the essential pawn structure. Black's king is very safe and almost impossible to attack. So Black can play more actively with the queen and rook }
41... Ra3 42. Ra2 Rb3 43. Ra8+ Kg7 { Black could then rush the h-pawn up the board to create some weaknesses and pressure the dark squares, at no risk of weakening his own kingside. } *


