{ This is a very common setup against the Maroczy Bind. Black wants to play a rook to c8 to add pressure to the c4 pawn. However, there is a correct rook to play to c8. }
14... Rfc8! (14... Rac8? { Rac8, the more "normal" looking move, is a big inaccuracy here. } 15. Nd5! Qxd2 16. Nxe7+! { And White wins a pawn with this sneaky intermezzo. Notice if BLack had played Rfc8 instead, the same line would not have worked due to Kf8 in response to the check, when the knight is being attacked. }) 15. Nd5?! Qxd2 16. Nxe7+ Kf8 { And Black wins the knight next move. } 17. Rxd2 (17. Nxg6+ hxg6 18. Rxd2 { A knight for two pawns }) 17... Kxe7 *


