1. e4 c5 2. b3 (2. b4 cxb4 3. a3 d5 4. exd5 Qxd5 { Active position, and Black is still up a pawn } 5. axb4?? Qe5+) (2. a3 g6 3. b4 Bg7 { Bogus. Black is doing well, end of discussion }) 2... g6 3. Bb2 Nf6 4. e5 Nd5 5. e6 (5. c4 Nc7 6. e6 f6 7. exd7+ Bxd7) 5... f6 { Black will get quick development and a space advantage in the center. No troubles } 6. exd7+ Bxd7 7. Nf3 e5 8. Bc4 Nb6 9. Be2 Bg7 { Nice center there for Black! } *


