1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nc3 Bg7 6. Be3 Nf6 7. f3?! { This is a weak move. I'm surprised it is still so commonly played. Well, that could be good news. I will teach you how to destroy anyone who plays f3. } 7... O-O 8. Qd2 { White's calmly entering the Yugoslav Attack of the Sicilian Dragon right? Wrong! The difference is you haven't pushed your d-pawn yet. } 8... d5! { The key part of the refutation. If you play 8. d6, White will play Bc4 next and the game will indeed transpose back to the Yugoslav Attack, which White probably is booked up on 15 moves in. } 9. exd5 (9. O-O-O dxe4 10. Nxc6 Qxd2+ 11. Rxd2 bxc6 12. Nxe4 (12. fxe4 Ng4 13. Bc5 Bh6) 12... Nd5 13. Bc5 Bh6) (9. Nxc6 bxc6 10. exd5 Nxd5 11. Nxd5 cxd5 12. c3 a5 (12... Rb8 13. Bxa7 Rxb2 14. Qxb2 Qa5 15. Rc1 Qxa7)) 9... Nxd5 10. Nxd5 Qxd5 11. Nxc6 Qxc6 12. c3 Bf5 *


