1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. c4 Nf6 6. Nc3 d6 7. Nc2 { Nc2 is a sideline in the Maroczy, with the overarching idea to keep more pieces on the board to full utilize White's space advantage. } 7... Bg7 8. Be2 Nd7 { Innocent looking move, but the threat is to play Bxc3, which creates double isolated pawns for White. } 9. O-O (9. Bd2 { Preventing the doubling of c-pawns } 9... O-O 10. O-O Nc5 11. b4 (11. f3 f5 12. b4 Ne6) 11... Bxc3 12. Bxc3 Nxe4 13. Bb2 e5) 9... Bxc3!? 10. bxc3 Nc5 11. Bh6 f6 *


