1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. c4 Nf6 6. Nc3 d6 7. Be2 Nxd4 8. Qxd4 Bg7 9. Bg5 { 9. Bg5 is very similar to the 9. Be3 variation. } 9... O-O 10. Qd2 a5 { Same multipurpose plan } 11. O-O a4 12. Rac1 Qa5 13. Rfd1 Be6 14. f3 (14. Nd5 Bxd5 15. exd5 Ne4 { Illustrating the difference with the Bg5. Now there is a triple attack and White is under pressure from the long diagonal. } 16. Qxa5 Rxa5 17. Bxe7 Re8 18. Bh4 Bxb2 19. Rb1 a3!) 14... Rfc8 15. Nb5 Qxd2 { As usual, Black should be happy to trade queens because of the space deficit. } 16. Rxd2 Kf8 { Black has no real weaknesses for White to exploit. Future plans could involve Nd7-c5 or double up rooks on the c-file. } *


