1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 g6 5. c4 Nf6 6. Nc3 Nxd4 7. Qxd4 d6 8. Be3 Bg7 9. Be2 O-O 10. Qd2 a5 11. O-O a4 12. f3 Qa5 13. Rac1 Be6 14. Rc2 Rfc8 15. b4 axb3 (15... Qxb4? { Black cannot capture because the queen will get chased around and make unnecessary committal moves to avoid getting trapped } 16. Rb1 Qa5 (16... Qa3 17. Nb5) 17. Bb6 Qe5 18. Rb5) 16. axb3 Qb4 17. Na4 Qxb3 18. Nb6 Bh6 { Great intermezzo. } 19. f4 (19. Bxh6 Qxb6+) 19... Nxe4 20. Qd3 Qxd3 21. Bxd3 Ra3 22. Bxe4 Rxe3 23. Nxc8 Rxe4 24. Nxe7+ Kf8 25. Nd5 { White is up a rook for minor piece and pawn. However, because Black's minor pieces make up the bishop pair, the evaluation is still far from clear. } 25... b5 { Undermining the d5 outpost, so to restrict the knight some more. } 26. Rd1 bxc4 27. Nc3 Rxf4 28. Rxd6 Rf5 29. Nd1 Ra5 30. Kf2 Rf5+ 31. Ke1 Rc5 32. g3 Bg5 33. Nc3 Bf5 34. Ra2 Re5+ 35. Re2 Ra5 36. Ra2 Rc5 37. h4 Be7 38. Rda6 Re5+ 39. Re2 Bb4! { 0-1 White resigns. } 0-1


