[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Most Common Mistakes in Chess"]
[ChapterName "Mistake 11: Being too materialistic"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/xx2nOKJv/aeELYde8"]
[FEN "1k1r3r/ppp2p2/3p3q/3Pp2p/2N1P1pP/2P5/PP3QKP/5R2 b - - 2 24"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2020.07.21"]
[UTCTime "03:10:33"]

{ Black is up an exchange (rook for knight) and an extra pawn. It is important to be willing to give some material back if necessary to achieve a decisive advantage. }
24... Rhf8 (24... f5! { Giving back a pawn to free up the position and shut down the f5 outpost from White's knight. } 25. exf5 (25. Qxf5 Rdf8) 25... Rhf8 26. Ne3 e4 { And Black is still up a healthy exchange and a more active position. }) 25. Ne3 Qh7 26. Nf5 { It is unclear how Black can make progress with this annoying knight on f5, which arguably is stronger than a rook at the moment. } *


[Event "🔥🔥: Mistake 12: Not thinking ahead"]
[Site "https://lichess.org/study/fNOVLINj/rjPbFftz"]
[Date "2020.07.21"]
[Result "*"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Mr_Penings"]
[Variant "From Position"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Most Common Mistakes in Chess"]
[ChapterName "Mistake 12: Not thinking ahead"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/xx2nOKJv/dO8oCWI7"]
[FEN "r5k1/1pqbbpp1/2p1pn1p/2Pn4/1P1PN3/5N1P/2QBBPP1/1R4K1 w - - 0 19"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2020.07.21"]
[UTCTime "03:10:33"]

19. b5? { Not a bad idea to expand on the queenside, but clearly White did not think ahead. After the series of exchanges, Black trades off the horrendous light squared bishop and has more breathing room. } (19. Ne5! { Instead, focus on improving your own pieces. Advance the knight to the powerful centralized square e5. Black has to find a way to untangle in their limited space. }) 19... cxb5 20. Bxb5 Bxb5 21. Rxb5 { Black is fine now (if not better!) } *


[Event "🔥🔥: Mistake 13: Not considering all variations of a tactic"]
[Site "https://lichess.org/study/fNOVLINj/odjfalWF"]
[Date "2020.07.21"]
[Result "*"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Mr_Penings"]
[Variant "From Position"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Most Common Mistakes in Chess"]
[ChapterName "Mistake 13: Not considering all variations of a tactic"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/xx2nOKJv/zIZhJGWr"]
[FEN "r1b2rk1/p1pnqppp/1pn1p3/4P3/8/P1PB2N1/2P1QPPP/R1B1K2R w KQ - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2020.07.21"]
[UTCTime "03:10:33"]

1. Bxh7+? { White sees a tactic to win a pawn... Slow down! Most tactics have another variation with a move order difference } (1. Qe4! { This move order simply wins the knight on c6. Black cannot protect the knight and stop checkmate on h7 }) 1... Kxh7 2. Qe4+ Kg8 3. Qxc6 { White has just won a pawn, and it's debatable if it has helped White or not. The loss of the bishop leads to severe damage to the light squares } 3... Ba6! *


