[UTCTime "03:10:33"]

{ From the famous game Aronian - Kramnik in 2018 Candidates }
7. h3?! Rg8! { Kramnik uses the h3 pawn as a hook to smash open the g-file. You should definitely check out this game if you haven't already. It will make all the history books! } 8. Kh1 Nh5 9. c3 g5 10. Nxe5 g4 { And Black is just crushing } *


[Event "🔥🔥: Mistake 15: Blindly following general chess principles"]
[Site "https://lichess.org/study/fNOVLINj/ZJ2OcNxQ"]
[Date "2020.07.21"]
[Result "*"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Mr_Penings"]
[Variant "From Position"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Most Common Mistakes in Chess"]
[ChapterName "Mistake 15: Blindly following general chess principles"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/xx2nOKJv/MMAzQvYL"]
[FEN "r4k2/pp2q2p/2npb1p1/2p5/2P1P3/2NP2P1/P5BP/1R1Q2K1 w - - 0 16"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2020.07.21"]
[UTCTime "03:10:33"]

{ The general rule is knights belong on outposts. d5 is an outpost by definition, and a common mistake is to blindly follow these principles. }
16. Nd5? (16. e5! { A better continuation to achieve the superior minor piece } 16... dxe5 (16... Nxe5?! 17. Rxb7) 17. Bxc6 bxc6 18. Qf3+) 16... Bxd5 17. exd5 Nd4 { Wait a second... now black has the knight on an outpost and White has a terrible bishop. White gets punished for blindly following the rules without second thought. } *


[Event "🔥🔥: Mistake 16: Giving up too early"]
[Site "https://lichess.org/study/fNOVLINj/mHc3MYKL"]
[Date "2020.07.21"]
[Result "*"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Mr_Penings"]
[Variant "From Position"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Most Common Mistakes in Chess"]
[ChapterName "Mistake 16: Giving up too early"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/xx2nOKJv/kU6AdU7v"]
[FEN "4b3/5pk1/p3p1p1/Np1pP1Kp/nP1B1P2/P2P3P/6P1/8 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2020.07.21"]
[UTCTime "03:10:33"]

{ Although the material is even, Black is seemingly down a full knight since the Na4 is completely restricted by the Bd4 and the bishop on c8 is locked up. While White should be winning this eventually, Black should still watch for tricks. }
1. Nb3 Bc6 2. Nd2 Be8 3. Nf1 Bc6 4. Ne3 Be8 5. g3 Bc6 6. Ng2? Be8 (6... Nc3!! 7. Bxc3 d4 { Leads to an opposite colored bishop endgame. Even though Black is down a pawn, White cannot win this. }) 7. f5 { And White eventually broke through on the kingside } *


[Event "🔥🔥: Mistake 17: Unaware of the dynamics of the position"]
[Site "https://lichess.org/study/fNOVLINj/mN9CZmJb"]
[Date "2020.07.21"]
[Result "*"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Mr_Penings"]
[Variant "From Position"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Most Common Mistakes in Chess"]
[ChapterName "Mistake 17: Unaware of the dynamics of the position"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/xx2nOKJv/cG9qalqd"]
[FEN "r1bqk2r/p3bppp/1pn5/2ppPp2/5P2/2NP1NP1/PPP4P/R1BQ1RK1 b kq - 3 10"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2020.07.21"]
[UTCTime "03:10:33"]

{ Black has the bishop pair, and wisely should control the h1-a8 diagonal. }
10... Bb7? { The right idea, but it fails because White closes the diagonal first with d4 } (10... d4! { Playing d4 first is a must here if Black wants to control the long diagonal. Knight is forced to move, and only then is Bb7 accurate } 11. Ne2 Bb7) 11. d4 cxd4 12. Nb5 { And the diagonal is now shut down for as long as White desires. } *


[Event "🔥🔥: Mistake 18: Unequal trades against higher rated players"]
[Site "https://lichess.org/study/fNOVLINj/LZiuG5LY"]
[Date "2020.07.21"]
[Result "*"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Mr_Penings"]
[Variant "From Position"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Most Common Mistakes in Chess"]
[ChapterName "Mistake 18: Unequal trades against higher rated players"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/xx2nOKJv/4HR51Ma4"]
[FEN "4rrk1/pp3p1p/2p3p1/3p4/P7/1P1P4/2P2PPP/4RRK1 b - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2020.07.21"]
[UTCTime "03:10:33"]

{ It is very common for lower rated players to aim to swap off all the pieces as fast as possible. But beware, not all trades are equal. }
1... Rxe1? { Trading first allows White to control the file, a critical factor in an otherwise dead drawn endgame } (1... a5 2. f3 f6 { Dead draw after Kf7 and then swapping off all the rooks. }) 2. Rxe1 f6 3. Re7 Rf7 4. Re6 Kf8 5. g4 { This endgame is far from easy to hold. Black cannot easily play Re7 nor move the king upwards. Only White has the winning chances here. } *


[Event "🔥🔥: Mistake 19: Rushing the attack"]
[Site "https://lichess.org/study/fNOVLINj/jGZRo0JK"]
[Date "2020.07.21"]
[Result "*"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Mr_Penings"]
[Variant "From Position"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Most Common Mistakes in Chess"]
[ChapterName "Mistake 19: Rushing the attack"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/xx2nOKJv/T8kDWLOD"]
[FEN "5bk1/pppb2rp/3p1n2/3Pp1qn/2P2p2/5Q1P/PPBB1PP1/R5RK b - - 11 24"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2020.07.21"]
[UTCTime "03:10:33"]

24... Bg4? { Unnecessarily complication the position. This moves looks pretty, but it can easily backfire. } (24... Qh4! { Slow and simple. Sometimes, the patient move is the strongest. Black prepares Bg4 next, and there will be no complications. Meanwhile, White cannot find any useful move to stop Black's attack. } { [%cal Gd7g4] }) 25. hxg4 Ng3+ { Black attempts at fireworks, but unfortunately, this move fails due to a shocking move. } 26. Qxg3! { If Black takes the queen, his own queen will be lost too. } *


[Event "🔥🔥: Mistake 20: Too scared to sacrifice material"]
[Site "https://lichess.org/study/fNOVLINj/NNR9bsyo"]
[Date "2020.07.21"]
[Result "*"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Mr_Penings"]
[Variant "From Position"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Most Common Mistakes in Chess"]
[ChapterName "Mistake 20: Too scared to sacrifice material"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/xx2nOKJv/c4kFVjPh"]
[FEN "r1b1kb1r/2qn1p1p/p2ppp2/1p6/3NPPP1/2N5/PPP1Q2P/2KR1B1R b kq - 1 11"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2020.07.21"]
[UTCTime "03:11:31"]

11... b4 12. Na4? (12. Nd5! { The thematic Nd5 sacrifice in the Sicilian. White will not have any clear cut win, but there is more than enough compensation for the lost knight. } 12... exd5 13. exd5+ Be7 14. Re1 Nb8 15. h4 { Black's king is stuck in the center and pieces are completely tangled up. (Baadur Jobava - Holden Hernandez 2008) }) 12... Nc5 { Black is now totally fine. } *


