[UTCTime "18:24:24"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 b6 5. Bd3 Bb7 6. Nf3 h6 { Not a logical move here, but I'm trying to show a fairly common mistake amongst newer players. } 7. O-O d6?? { Always be on the lookout for Qa4+, which forks the king and bishop. Rule of thumb: Castle early, but if you play d6 before 0-0, you must have a good reason and only if Qa4+ fails. } 8. Qa4+ Nc6 9. d5 { Black loses a minor in all lines } 9... Bxc3 10. dxc6 *


