1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 Bb4+ 4. Bd2 a5 5. Bg2 d6 6. Nf3 Nbd7 7. O-O e5 8. Bg5 exd4 9. Nxd4 h6 10. Bf4 O-O 11. Qc2 a4 { Thematic a4 to grab the c5 outpost for the near future } 12. Rd1 Nb6 13. Nc3 Qe7 14. Qd3 Bc5 15. h3 c6 16. Rab1 d5 { Accepting an isolated d-pawn but white will have to give up the fianchetto bishop. } 17. cxd5 Nbxd5 18. Nxd5 Nxd5 19. Bxd5 cxd5 20. Kg2 Bxd4 21. Qxd4 Bf5 22. Rbc1 Qxe2 { In opposite colored bishop middlegames, the side with the stronger attack with their bishop usually wins. That is because the bishops cannot contest each other and are playing separate games. } 23. Rd2 Be4+ 24. Kh2 Qf3 25. Rg1 { Black is winning the battle of the bishops! } 25... g5 26. Bd6 Rfc8 27. Qe3 Qxe3 28. fxe3 Ra6 29. Be5 Rac6 30. Rgd1 h5 31. h4 Bf3 32. Rf1 Rc2 33. Rdf2 Be2 34. Re1 Bd3 35. Rxc2 Rxc2+ 36. Kg1 g4 37. a3 Be4 38. Rd1 f6 39. Bxf6 Rg2+ 40. Kf1 Rxg3 41. Bg5 Rh3 { 0-1 White resigns. } 0-1


