{ This type of position is reached in many of the advanced variations. }
1... h5 { An important move to prevent White from playing g4 and start to establish a nice outpost on f5 for a knight. } 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bd3 Nh6 { Black welcomes an exchange of light squared bishops, so the knight can now occupy f5. The c5 pawn break is next and Black gets a very comfortable middlegame. } { [%cal Gc6c5] } *


