{ Caro-Kann players must be ready to play against isolated queen pawn positions, which arise after majority of the c4 lines. Overarching principle: Trade minor pieces and blockade the d5 square so White doesn't ever push d5. }
1... Nf6 2. a3 b6 { Finishing development and then lining up rooks on the d- and c- files to exert more pressure in the center. See Judit Polgar - Anatoly Karpov game below for an illustration of middlegame plans for both sides. } *


