{ Nice miniature win by US Grandmaster Nakamura which nicely illustrates the potential dangers of a kingside attack with the open h-file. }
1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Bf5 5. Ng3 Bg6 6. Nh3 Nf6 7. Nf4 Nbd7 8. Bc4 Qc7 9. O-O e6 10. c3 Bd6 11. Qf3 c5 12. dxc5 Bxc5 13. Bb3 O-O-O 14. Nxg6 { A move I'm sure White regretted after the game. The h-file looks deadly even to an intermediate level player! } 14... hxg6 15. Bf4 e5 16. Be3 e4 { A possible rook sac coming?! } 17. Qe2 Bxe3 18. Qxe3 (18. fxe3 Rxh2 { Rxh2 is coming either way }) 18... Rxh2 19. Rfd1 Rdh8 20. Qxa7 e3 21. Qxe3 Ng4 { White resigns 0-1. Try to find the mating pattern if White plays Qd2. } 0-1


