{ The "cousin" of the Queens Gambit Declined is the Slav (d4 d5 c4 c6) and similarly, we do not allow Slav players into their comfort zone! }
1. c4 c6 2. e4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. cxd5 Nf6 { Bb5+ and Qa4+ are both very theory heavy lines, which are great lines. Nc3 is the line I recommend since it is more about ideas and not about memorizing many moves of theory. } (4... Qxd5 { Free tempo on the queen, which cannot be better than 4. Nf6. Usually results in similar positions but down a tempo } 5. Nc3 Qa5 6. Nf3) 5. Nc3 Nxd5 6. Nf3 Nc6 7. Bb5 e6 8. O-O Be7 9. d4 O-O 10. Re1 Bf6 (10... a6 11. Bxc6 bxc6 12. Ne5) (10... Bd7 11. Bd3) 11. a3 Bd7 12. Bd3 g6 13. Bh6 Re8 14. Bc2 { The main plans involve a kingside attack and stabilizing the central pawns. Sometimes, a pawn rush with h4-h5 is played to even further weaken Black's kingside structure. } *


