1. c4 b6 2. Nc3 Bb7 3. e4 (3. d4 e6 4. a3 f5 5. d5 { This line is also playable, though it is a d4 opening. See Le Quang Liem - Vitaly Kunin below for a sample game in this line if you are interested. It blocks the fianchettoed bishop for as long as possible. } 5... Nf6 6. g3) 3... e6 4. Nge2 Nf6 (4... Bb4 5. g3 f5 6. Bg2 Nf6 7. d3 { See Chapter 39 (DanielHe2200 - Fast_Chance) for a solid game in this line. }) 5. d3 c5 (5... d5 6. cxd5 exd5 7. e5 d4 (7... Nfd7 8. d4 c5 9. Be3 { Black's fianchetto bishop is blocked and you have a nice space advantage }) 8. Qa4+ Qd7 9. Nxd4 Qxa4 10. Nxa4) 6. g3 d5 7. exd5 exd5 8. Bg2 Be7 9. O-O O-O 10. Nf4 { With good pressure along the h1-a8 diagonal and the d5 square. } *


