{ Here are all of the rare and offbeat (synonyms for bad) lines against 1. c4. }
1. c4 d5 { A fine first move against just about every first move except the English. Gives up a central pawn for a flank pawn. Can't be good } (1... g5 2. d4 { If you do see 1. g5, just go tranpose into a d4 line. This cannot be any good. }) (1... Nc6 { Weird, but a reasonable move. This would normally transpose back to one of the above lines. } 2. Nc3 e5 3. g3 { Back to the c4 e5 lines. }) 2. cxd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qd8 4. d4 { Two central pawns. Cannot ask for more } *


