1. f3 e6 2. g4 (2. Be3 b5 { This will transpose to the Be3 variation. } 3. g4 (3. Qd2 { [%cal Ge1c1,Gb8d7,Gd7b6,Gf6d7] }) 3... h6 4. h4 b4 5. Nce2 e5 6. Nb3 d5! { The common theme of striking back in the center whenever you are faced with a flank attack! }) 2... h6 { The idea is to prevent White's expansion too much. White could play h4, but g5 is still not playable due to the undefended rook on h1. } 3. h4 d5 { Striking back in the center. } *


