1. Bd3 { A popular move at the lower levels, but harmless! I recommend switching to a kingside fianchetto to limit the range of the Bd3 and also hit the unprotected knight on d4 } 1... g6 2. O-O Bg7 { Also eyeing the undefended knight on d4 } 3. h3 (3. Be3? Ng4 4. h3 Nxe3 5. fxe3 O-O) 3... O-O 4. Be3 b5 5. a3 Bb7 { As seen in Theme #5, this is a comfortable position for Black. Nbd7 is next followed by Nc5 or Nb6-Nc4. } *


