1. Rg1!? { Looks ridiculous, but this is indeed a legitimate line for White. The idea is as obvious as it seems: g4! } 1... b5 2. g4 Bb7 3. Bg2 Nfd7 4. Be3 e6 { I don't recommend anything too crazy against the Rg1 line. Just play normally and reroute the Nf6 to the queenside, making White's early g4 questionable since there are no easy pawn breaks on the kingside. } { [%cal Gd7b6,Gd7b8,Gb6c4] } *


