[UTCTime "02:16:38"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6 6. Be3 Bg7 7. f3 O-O 8. Qd2 Nc6 9. Bc4 Bd7 10. O-O-O Rc8 11. Bb3 Ne5 12. h4 Nc4 (12... h5 { h5 is the main line in the sharp Sicilian Dragon for logical reason: Allowing White to play h5 is simply too dangerous. }) 13. Bxc4 Rxc4 14. h5! { Sacrificing the h-pawn to open up the h-file with 2 tempi. Again, using the bluff concept. Black accepts the gambit and also the consequences of White's now open h-file. Or else White will play hxg6 anyways } 14... Nxh5 15. g4 Nf6 (15... Ng3? 16. Rhg1 { Knight is trapped here }) 16. Nde2 { Solidifying the center before pursuing the Bh6 kingside attack. } (16. Bh6? { Bh6 right away runs into some problems with the loose Nd4. } 16... Nxe4) *


