[UTCTime "02:16:38"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. e3 Bg7 5. h4 O-O (5... h5 { Black is advised to play h5 to avoid the onslaught altogether. }) 6. h5 Nxh5 7. Rxh5! gxh5 8. Qxh5 { Although White is down an exchange, this position is arguably already winning for White, with a huge score in practice. All of White's pieces will jump in the attack, while Black's are all in hiding on the back rank. } 8... c6 9. Bd3 f5 10. Nf3 Qe8 11. Qh2 { White will castle long and play Rh1 with a decisive attack. } { [%cal Ge1c1] } *


