{ Here is a must-know trap commonly seen in the Classical Variation, but it is prevalent in many of these setups. }
1. Be2? { Seemingly normal, but it is a mistake since White's pawn structure falls real quick, and tactics favor Black. } 1... cxd4 2. Nxd4 Ndxe5! 3. fxe5 (3. Nxc6 Nxc6! { The boomerang knight snatches a pawn in the process }) 3... Qh4+ { Picking up a pawn and White's e5 pawn will soon fall as well. } *


