1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. c3 Nc6 5. Nf3 Nge7 6. a3 Nf5 7. b4 cxd4 8. cxd4 Bd7 9. g4 (9. Bb2 b5!? 10. Bxb5 Nxe5 { Windmill technique at play }) 9... Nh4 { The perks of not playing Qb6 is Nh4 is now playable, making g4 an awkward move for White. } *


